                    "With the appointment of AJ Nelson as the team’s new assistant head coach, and the addition of four new first-years, the team held substantial potential going into the fall season. The Lions delivered in their first tournament of the year, winning six titles at the Columbia Women’s Tennis Invitational. Two of the doubles matches came down to all-Columbia finals. ",
