                    "In their season-opening weekend, the Lions defeated No. 11-ranked Butler 2-1. Junior John Denis was named Ivy League Player of the Week after scoring a goal against Butler and notching an assist in a game against West Point. Facing off against Binghamton, senior captain Kynan Rocks scored a hat trick, leading the team to a shutout of the Bearcats. ",
                    "As Ivy play began, senior goalkeeper Dylan Castanheira blocked six attempts on goal to secure Columbia’s 3-1 win against Brown. The Light Blue went on to beat Penn 2-0 in its second match of conference play with goals from senior Dylan Mott and senior defender Nick Azuma. However, the team’s early success was soon followed by an emotional 2-0 loss to Princeton. ",
                    "The Lions were clearly unfazed, as they defeated Yale, Dartmouth, and Harvard shortly thereafter. Mott’s dominance on the field was undeniable in the game against Harvard, where he scored a brace. ",
                    "In the final match of the season, the team fell in overtime to Cornell, cementing its second-place finish in the Ivy League. Though Denis opened the scoring with a goal in the 59th minute, the Big Red managed to pull one back in regulation, putting the game away with a goal just six minutes into extra time. ",
                    "Castanheira was eventually signed by Atlanta United and was awarded All-Ivy League academic honors alongside Markarian. ",
