                    "For the first time since 2015, the Light Blue defeated Yale 2-0. Schildkraut made the first goal of the day with an assist from Anderson. Hemmings secured the win with a shot in the 58th minute of the game. However, the team was unable to replicate its success, falling to Harvard 2-1 in its season closer. The loss at Harvard led women’s soccer to lock down a fifth-place finish in the Ivy League, ending the season with a record of 8-7-1, 4-3 Ivy. ",
                    "Despite its lackluster results in Ivy play, the Light Blue brought several honors back to Morningside Heights. Junior defender Amalya Johnson won her third consecutive First Team All-Ivy honors and was selected for the NCAA Division I Women's All-East Region third team. This award marks the ninth time in program history that a member of Columbia women’s soccer was named to All-Region honors. Anderson and Johnson were both selected for the NCAA Division I Women’s Scholar All-East Region Team, a first for the program since 2013. ",
